channel.title: Young Couple Gaming: Pokémon GO Podcast
channel.itunes:subtitle: A Young Couple talking about the Pocket Monsters on their phones and the places they go.
channel.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
channel.itunes:summary: Young Couple Gaming: Pokémon GO Podcast is a show about Adam and Taylor’s adventures with the popular mobile game, Pokémon GO! Weekly, they discuss Pokémon GO news and their recent adventures within the game.

item.itunes:title: "The Inaugural Episode"
item.title: YCG:PGP 001 - "The Inaugural Episode"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
Well, we said we were going to do it, and we did it. Welcome to the first episode of the Young Couple Gaming: Pokémon GO Podcast! In this episode, we introduce ourselves, recap the Larvitar Community Day, give our opinions on the Water Fest, and look forward to the news about the Summer Tour Global Challenge.
Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.itunes:title: "Back At It Again"
item.title: YCG:PGP 002 - "Back At It Again"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
We're back at it and managed to not give up after one episode. In this one, we talk about the newly announced community day, discuss the newest raid “bosses”, forget that Dortmund, Germany is a thing this weekend, make a hot and oh so wrong take on Snorlax research tasks in July, get excited about the new Alola boys in the wild, and go over the newest update which brings along trading and friends! Please, please be our friend.
Opening and Closing Song from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.itunes:title: "Tongue Twisters and Shiny Mewthree?!"
item.title: YCG:PGP 003 - "Tongue Twisters and Shiny Mewthree?!"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
Welcome to the shiny Mewthree episode! In this one, we discuss our thoughts on friendship and trading after a week of having it in the game, recap the Dortmund Safari Zone event, and slightly spoil the upcoming GO Fest. Other talking points include "planning" for Articuno Day, sunglasses Squirtle, and body slamming Snorlax with the new research tasks.
And a happy 4th of July to our fellow Americans! USA! USA! USA!
Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.itunes:title: "Wild Bagon Outside"
item.title: YCG:PGP 004 - "Wild Bagon Outside"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
It was a long and exhausting Pokémon GO weekend, so unwind with this weekend recap. We surprise you with the 2 year celebration summer Pikachu, raiding during Articuno hours talk show, have a hot take on NOT Squirtle Squad Community Day, get excited and nervous for Pokémon GO Fest, reitirate how hard it is to hatch Alolan Vulpix, and talk about some money money money money.... money.
Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.itunes:title: "The Generation 4 Zapdos Community Hours"
item.title: YCG:PGP 005 - "The Generation 4 Zapdos Community Hours"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:

Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.itunes:title: "Finally a #PokemonGOFest2018 Recap"
item.title: YCG:PGP 006 - "Finally a #PokemonGOFest2018 Recap"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
Remember that second episode from last week? Well, here it is. Finally, we have our #PokemonGOFest2018 recap for you. If you want to be told how great a weekend of Pokemon GO is in Chicago then listen in. Don't worry though, we do discuss the negatives and how GO Fest can get better in the future!
Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.itunes:title: "Alola Bois and Bad Jokes"
item.title: YCG:PGP 007 - "Alola Bois and Bad Jokes"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
Not only do we have a new episode for you, but we have terrible jokes in it as well! This week, we correct our ever so wrong guess at the new Regi raid boss, but guess what? Registeel is just as boring as Regirock, so we spend more time getting excited about the Alola raid bosses instead and ponder who is giving Raichu all of these pancakes!? We also have a new update in Pokémon GO involving friend list sorting and lucky Pokémon, which Taylor has been unlucky with getting. Lastly, we get excited about Raikou and reminisce on the Zapdos Hours.
Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops

item.title: YCG:PGP 008 - "Trade those Eevees for PVP"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
Get pumped for the most not exciting news week in YCG:PGP history. You can trade on the cheap right now, spin some stops for Spinda, don't stress over Eevee Community Days, and get not excited about PVP. We make up for the boring news week with our charm and singing.

item.itunes:title: "Hot Take Celeri Special Research"
item.title: YCG:PGP 009 - "Hot Take Bug Special Research"
item.itunes:author: Young Couple Gaming
item.itunes:subtitle:
We are back after our 2 week hiatus, but hey life happens right? In this episode, we try to catch up on all the things that we have missed in the game! Some of those things include Eevee and Chikorita Community Day, the new and wonderful bugs found in the game, the long awaited Celery/Broccoli Special Research that is buggy as well, the exciting raid boss Ho-oh (we guess Regirock too), and wrap it all up talking about the Johto Festival and World Championships. If you like hot takes this will be the episode for you.
Opening and Closing Song Taken from the Pokémon Go Remix - IT'S TIME TO GO! - Dj CUTMAN ft. CG5 from GameChops
